  <main class="wrap">
    <div class="article-hero">
      <h1 style="text-align:center">Independent reviews, transparent methodology.</h1>
    </div>

    <div class="prose">
      <p>SpykeVision is an independent, reader-supported home-theater publication. I review projectors the way I'd want them reviewed: with real measurements, full transparency about test conditions, and no marketing spin. If a number looks too good or too bad, I tell you why, and how I measured it.</p>

      <h2>How I measure</h2>
      <p>Every review is built on a consistent bench process so results are comparable across products:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Brightness:</strong> measured in manufacturer-calibrated picture modes, across the full zoom and aperture range, after thermal stabilization.</li>
        <li><strong>Native contrast:</strong> Full on/off, per zoom and aperture position.</li>
        <li><strong>ANSI contrast:</strong> 8×8 pattern, measured at both centered and shifted lens positions.</li>
        <li><strong>ADL contrast:</strong> across scene brightness levels from On/Off through 50% (ANSI).</li>
        <li><strong>Optics:</strong> sharpness patterns, distortion via laser level, uniformity maps, and lens-shift behavior.</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="note">The test pattern, meter, and conditions are documented alongside each chart — so anyone can reproduce a measurement. Spotted something off? Write to me — corrections are published openly.</div>

      <h2>Get in touch</h2>
      <p>Reviews also appear on <a href="https://www.avsforum.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">AVS Forum</a> — a good place to discuss results. Want to submit a product for review or have questions about published content? Reach out on the forum or via the <a href="/contact/">contact form</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </main>
</Base>
